<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>HTML Table Example</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Working of HTML Tables</h2>

<table border="1">
    
    <!-- Heading Row with colspan -->
    <tr>
        <th colspan="3">Student Details</th>
    </tr>

    <!-- Column Headings -->
    <tr>
        <th>Roll No</th>
        <th>Name</th>
        <th>Marks</th>
    </tr>

    <!-- Normal Row -->
    <tr>
        <td>32</td>
        <td>Lavanya</td>
        <td>81</td>
    </tr>

    <!-- Rowspan Example -->
    <tr>
        <td rowspan="2">2</td>
        <td>Durga</td>
        <td>90</td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
        <td>Durga (Practical)</td>
        <td>88</td>
    </tr>

</table>

<p><b>Explanation:</b></p>
<p>
&lt;table&gt; creates a table.<br>
&lt;tr&gt; creates a row.<br>
&lt;th&gt; creates a heading cell.<br>
&lt;td&gt; creates a data cell.<br>
border attribute adds border.<br>
colspan merges columns.<br>
rowspan merges rows.
</p>

</body>
</html>